methods.get:
Gets the object in row i of the column.

:param i: (int) - index
:return: (java.lang.Object) object in row i of the column
methods.getColumnName:
Gets the column's name.

:return: (java.lang.String) name of the column being held
methods.getDouble:
Gets the object in row i of the column as a double.

:param i: (int) - index
:return: (double) column's value at row i as a double
methods.getTableHandle:
Gets the handle for the underlying table.

:return: (io.deephaven.db.plot.util.tables.TableHandle) handle for the table
methods.size:
Gets the number of rows in the column.

:return: (int) size of the column
methods.type:
Gets the data type of the column.

:return: (java.lang.Class) column's data type
methods.typeClassification:
Gets the column's ColumnHandlerFactory.TypeClassification.

:return: (io.deephaven.db.plot.util.tables.ColumnHandlerFactory.TypeClassification) column's ColumnHandlerFactory.TypeClassification

text: Holds a table column. Allows access to the column's data and the underlying table.
